<% content_for :page_title do %>
  Accessibility -
<% end %>

<main role="main" tabindex="-1" id="content">
  <%= render partial: 'layouts/feedback_survey_banner' if flash[:beta_message] == 'hide'%>

  <h1 class="heading-large">
    Accessibility
  </h1>

  <p>The website doesn’t have a separate accessibility statement. This is because we’re constantly working to make data.gov.uk as accessible and usable as possible for every user.</p>

  <p>You can read a blog about <%= link_to 'accessibility at GDS', 'https://accessibility.blog.gov.uk/' %>.</p>

  <h2 class="heading-medium">
    Compatibility with tools
  </h2>

  <p>Data.gov.uk is designed to be compatible with recent versions of the following screen readers:</p>

  <ul class="list list-bullet">
    <li>JAWS</li>
    <li>NVDA</li>
    <li>VoiceOver</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The site is also designed to be compatible with:</p>

  <ul class="list list-bullet">
    <li>basic operating system screen magnifiers, such as ZoomText magnifier</li>
    <li>speech recognition software, such as Dragon Naturally Speaking</li>
    <li>operating system speech packages</li>
  </ul>


  <h2 class="heading-medium">
    Get help
  </h2>

  <p>AbilityNet provides guidance about how to:</p>

  <ul class="list list-bullet">
    <li><%= link_to 'make your mouse easier to use', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/making-your-mouse-easier-to-use/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'use your keyboard instead of a mouse', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/category/keyboard-shortcuts/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'talk to your device', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/talking-to-your-device/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'make your device talk to you', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/category/making-your-mobile-or-tablet-talk/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'make text larger', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/making-text-larger/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'change your colours', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/changing-your-colours/', target: :blank %></li>
    <li><%= link_to 'magnify the screen', 'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/magnifying-the-screen/', target: :blank %></li>
  </ul>
</main>
